<title>FRANCE: Renault staff council delays job cut study.</title>
<headline>Renault staff council delays job cut study.</headline>
<dateline>PARIS 1997-03-13</dateline>
<text>
<p>Renault's staff council has postponed an examination of the carmaker's plan to cut 2,764 jobs in France to April 3 after the council secretary asked for expert comment on the plan, a company source said on Thursday.</p>
<p>&quot;Such a request is commonplace but it delays the examination of the plan by at least 28 days,&quot; the source said.</p>
<p>The council met on Thursday to study the plan amid union calls for one-labour stoppages at Renault's plants in France.</p>
<p>Renault recently announced plans to step up job cuts in France and close a Belgian assembly plant in Vilvoorde.</p>
<p>-- Paris Newsroom, +33 1 4221 5452</p>
